text: Thryptomene dampieri is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae that is endemic to Western Australia. The shrub in the Gascoyne and Pilbara regions of Western Australia between Shark Bay and Exmouth where it grows in sandy soils. ==References== dampieri Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Plants described in 2014 Category:Taxa named by Barbara Lynette Rye
title: Thryptomene dampieri
